Metadata: Construction on Wisconsin's Lake Michigan coast
"Coastal Engineering Practice '92 Proceedings," pp. 762-778, Long Beach, California, March 9-11, 1992.

This paper provides a preliminary evaluation of a set of 100 residential properties along Wisconsin's Lake Michigan coast; an examination of the vulnerability of coastal homes and adequacy of shore protection in terms of the risks of flooding, erosion and storm wave damage; and some examples of properties that have withstood high water and storm waves for many years.
